{
  "texts": [
    "Most of the existing augmentation methods are in input space.",
    "For example, augmentation on images includes rotation, cropping, and flipping, and text-domain augmentations include back translation 37 and synonym substitution 40.",
    "However, studies 41, 42 suggest that interpolations in hidden layers can capture more advanced information, enhancing semantic diversity and providing additional training signals.",
    "For example, enhancing diversity in latent spaces can improve the robustness of text generation models 43.",
    "Inspired by these insights, we introduce the SoftMix augmentation operation, designed to increase diversity and strengthen robustness by latent space augmentations."
  ]
}